"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-explainer-olympics-can-paris-2024-be-the-greenest-games-yet\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  FILE PHOTO: Paris 2024 Olympics - Preview - Paris, France - July 25, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2690211910779028e-13, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A person is cycling on an empty street ahead of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Peter Cziborra/File Photo    Published\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:01 AM  Updated\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:01 AM  LONDON - With medals made of iron salvaged from Eiffel Tower refurbishments and stadium seating of recycled plastic, Paris 2024 aims to be the greenest olympics yet.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The case for action is clear as scientists have said intense heat linked to man-made carbon emissions is a growing risk to competitors at the world's largest sporting event and beyond.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has pledged to reduce its carbon emissions by half compared to the average emitted during the London and Rio Summer Games.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9970232970259877, \"rank\": 0.0018852127795279184, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of Paris 2024's efforts towards meeting that goal.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CONSTRUCTION  For many people, Olympic stadiums such as Rio's Olympic Aquatic Centre that have failed to find a purpose after the Games symbolise extravagance.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"score\": 0.9990859639398125, \"rank\": 0.0007449144730968109, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\"}, {\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"score\": 0.9999998465305115, \"rank\": 1.5346933526662944e-07, \"text\": \"Olympic Aquatic Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has sought to minimise new construction.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all venues use existing or temporary sites, often relying on the city's landmarks as backdrops.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say the replacement of concrete with low carbon building materials, including sustainably-sourced wood, will reduce the Olympic Village's emissions by 30% compared to what the organisers referred to as conventional projects without giving details.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1490, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56247232913818e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent infrastructure accounted for 73% of the estimated 467,000 metric tons of carbon emissions generated by the Olympic Games between 2018 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, 11,000 seats at the only two purpose-built arenas for Paris 2024 are made out of recycled plastic.\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1841, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TRANSPORT  Along with construction, transport is expected to be one of the biggest sources of emissions during the Games.\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have said they will use low-carbon vehicles to ferry around athletes and official visitors and that all venues are accessible by bike, foot or public transport.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Paris is not tackling the emissions generated by spectators travelling to the Games - such emissions made up almost a third (28%) of the 3.3 million metric tons of carbon emitted by the London 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2626005063133335e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RENEWABLE POWER  Paris 2024 has said its venues will use renewable energy sources via the grid, rather than the diesel-powered generators often used at sporting venues.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 5,000 metres squared of solar panels have been installed on the roof of the Aquatics Centre and Olympic Village, and a 400 metre squared floating solar farm set up on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56247232913818e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Olympic Village has a cooling system that draws water from underground rather than air conditioning.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2773, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56247232913818e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"State-owned utility EDF told Reuters it would provide guarantees of origin to link the energy used by the Games to six wind and two solar production sites in France.\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 3040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2904, \"end\": 2911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.336168290922578e-12, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3033, \"end\": 3039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996728701606704, \"rank\": 0.00028189984655915427, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CARBON OFFSETS  To make up for the some of the emissions that are not being avoided, notably spectator air travel, Paris 2024 has purchased 1.3 million carbon credits.\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each credit represents one ton of emissions reduced or removed elsewhere - from projects protecting biodiversity-rich forests in Kenya and Guatemala and improving access to clean cooking in Kenya, Nigeria and the Democratic Republic of Congo.\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 5.8658286392706305e-12, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3349, \"end\": 3358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"score\": 0.9999791904752487, \"rank\": 2.074931217725108e-05, \"text\": \"Guatemala\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\"}, {\"begin\": 3400, \"end\": 3405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 5.8658286392706305e-12, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999981232577, \"rank\": 1.876525178251593e-09, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers are also spending 600,000 euros ($651,720.00) on four forestry projects in France to sequester 14,500 tons of greenhouse gases.\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3540, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996728701606704, \"rank\": 0.00028189984655915427, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although carbon credits can channel money to climate-friendly projects, often in the Global South, some credit-generating projects have been scrutinised over false claims about the benefits they deliver.\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 had positioned itself as the first climate-positive Games in reference to plans to remove, reduce or offset more emissions than it generates.\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has since dropped such claims, pledging instead to reduce its climate impact and support climate projects.\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 4061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Olympics  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4062, \"end\": 4069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 4113, \"end\": 4121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 4197, \"to\": 4211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4213, \"to\": 4230, \"entities\": []}]}"